<p>The <code>open</code> tag outputs the opening brace character.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}open{close}</pre>
<p>Result: {open}</p>

<h2>Show Variable Syntax</h2>
<pre>{open}open{close}$variableName{open}close{close}</pre>
<p>Result: {open}$variableName{close}</p>

<h2>Show Tag Syntax</h2>
<pre>{open}open{close}tagname{open}close{close}</pre>
<p>Result: {open}tagname{close}</p>

<h2>Document PAD Syntax</h2>
<pre>To show a variable, use {open}open{close}$name{open}close{close}</pre>
<p>Result: To show a variable, use {open}$name{close}</p>

<h2>Show Complete Tag</h2>
<pre>{open}open{close}if $count > 0{open}close{close}...{open}open{close}/if{open}close{close}</pre>
<p>Result: {open}if $count > 0{close}...{open}/if{close}</p>

<h2>Use in Documentation</h2>
<p>The open/close tags are commonly used throughout this documentation to show PAD syntax examples without the tags being processed.</p>
<table>
  <tr><th>Tag</th><th>Output</th></tr>
  <tr><td>{open}open{close}</td><td>{open}</td></tr>
  <tr><td>{open}close{close}</td><td>{close}</td></tr>
</table>
